ait\"\n|-\n|2014\n|''[[Delirium (Lauren Oliver novel)#Adaptation|Delirium]]''\n|Hana Tate\n|Unsold Fox pilot\n|-\n| 2014\n| ''[[Awkward (TV series)|Awkward]]''\n| Shayne\n| Episode: \"Prison Breaks\"\n|-\n| 2014\n| ''[[You're the Worst]]''\n| Dana\n| Episode: \"Equally Dead Inside\"\n|-\n| 2014\n| ''[[NCIS: Los Angeles]]''\n| Bonnie Flores\n| Episode: \"The Grey Man\"\n|-\n| 2016\n| ''[[Of Kings and Prophets]]''\n| [[Meirav|Merav]]\n| Main role; 9 episodes\n|-\n|2017\n|''Searchers''\n|Juniper\n|Television film\n|-\n|2017\n|''Ride Overshare''\n|Natalie\n|Episode: \"Natalie\"\n|-\n| 2017\n| ''[[Daytime Divas]]''\n| Nick\n| 2 episodes\n|-\n| 2017\n| ''[[Criminal Minds]]''\n| Helen Pierce\n| Episode: \"To a Better Place\"\n|-\n| 2017\u201318\n| ''[[Grey's Anatomy]]''\n| rowspan=\"2\" | Dr. Sam Bello\n| Recurring role; 12 episodes\n|-\n|2018\n|''Grey's Anatomy: B-Team''\n|[[American Broadcasting Company|ABC]] [[Web series|webseries]]; 3 episodes\n|-\n| 2019\u2013present\n| ''[[Roswell, New Mexico (TV series)|Roswell, New Mexico]]''\n| Liz Ortecho\n| Lead role\n|}\n\n==Awards==\n* '''2005''', 1st Place Overall High Score Teen Solo ''American Dance Awards''\n* '''2005''', Teen Elite Dancer and Capezio Ballet Award ''West Coast Dance Explosion''\n* '''2005''', 1st Runner-up [[Junior Orange Bowl]] Creative Writing Competition\n* '''2006''', Teen Elite Dancer ''West Coast Dance Explosion''\n* '''2006''', Teen High Score Solo & Teen Outstanding Dancer ''New York City Dance Alliance''\n* '''2006''', 1st Place Overall High Score Senior Solo & Hall of Fame Inductee ''Hall of Fame''\n* '''2006''', Ms. Teen Starquest ''Starquest''\n* '''2007''', Senior Outstanding Dancer ''New York City Dance Alliance''\n* '''2007''', Hall of Fame Inductee ''Hall of Fame''\n* '''2007''', Senior Dancer of the Year ''American Dance Awards''\n* '''2008''', Senior Outstanding Dancer & 1st Overall Senior Solo ''New York City Dance Alliance''\n* '''2008''', National Senior Jump VIP Winner ''Jump''\n* '''2008''', 1st Overall Senior Solo ''Star Systems''\n* '''2008''', Female Dancer of the Year & 1st Overall Senior Solo ''American Dance Awards''\n* '''2008''', 1st Overall Senior Solo ''Starquest''\n* '''2008''', 1st Overall Senior Solo ''Showbiz''\n* '''2008''', 1st Overall Senior Solo ''Hall of Fame''\n* '''2009''', Winner ''[[So You Think You Can Dance (season 5)|So You Think You Can Dance]]''\n\n==References==\n{{Reflist}}\n\n==External links==\n* {{Official website|http://www.jeaninemason.com}}\n* {{IMDb name|3471005}}\n\n{{s-start}}\n{{s-bef|before=[[Joshua Allen]]}}\n{{s-ttl|title = Winner of ''[[So You Think You Can Dance (season 5)|So You Think You Can Dance]]''|years = Summer 2009}}\n{{s-aft|after = [[Russell Ferguson]]}}\n{{s-end}}\n\n{{So You Think You Can Dance (American TV series)}}\n\n{{authority control}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Mason, Jeanine}}\n[[Category:1991 births]]\n[[Category:Living people]]\n[[Category:Actresses from Miami]]\n[[Category:American people of Cuban descent]]\n[[Category:American contemporary dancers]]\n[[Category:American television actresses]]\n[[Category:American film actresses]]\n[[Category:So You Think You Can Dance (American TV series) contestants]]\n[[Category:So You Think You Can Dance winners]]\n[[Category:Hispanic and Latino American actresses]]\n[[Category:People from Pinecrest, Florida]]\n[[Category:21st-century American actresses]]\n[[Category:21st-century American dancers]]\n", "text_old": "{{BLP sources|date=August 2014}}\n{{Infobox person\n| name               = Jeanine Mason\n| image              = -Jeanine Mason.jpg\n| image_size         = 200px\n| caption            = \n| birth_name         = Jeanine Marie Mason\n| birth_date         = {{birth date and age|1991|1|14}}\n| birth_place        = [[Miami, Florida]], U.S.\n| death_date         = \n| death_place        = \n| death_cause        = \n| resting_place      = \n| residence          = \n| other_names        = \n| known_for          = Winning ''[[So You Think You Can Dance (Season 5)|So You Think You Can Dance]]'': [[So You Think You Can Dance (Season 5)|Season 5]]; ''[[Bunheads]]''\n| education          = \n| employer           = \n| occupation         = Actress, dancer\n| years_active       = 2009\u2013present\n| title              = \n| salary             = \n| networth           = \n| height             = 5 ft 4 in<ref>{{cite web|url=http://content.blocagency.com/la/artist-content/dance/jeanine-mason/resume/bloc-jeanine-mason-resume.pdf|format=PDF|title=JEANINE MASON : AFTRA|website=Content.blocagency.com|accessdate=2017-08-21}}</ref>\n| term               = \n| boards             = \n| religion           = \n| spouse             = \n| partner            = \n| children           = \n| parents            = \n| relatives          = \n| website            = [http://www.jeaninemason.com/ jeaninemason.com]\n| footnotes          = \n}}\n\n'''Jeanine Marie Mason''' (born January 14, 1991)<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.instagram.com/p/Bd_YnkPA6Mt/|title=Thank you for all the birthday wishes. Man do I adore you all! Xo|date=January 14, 2018|access-date=May 13, 2018|work=[[Instagram]]|author=itsjeaninemason|language=en}}</ref> is an American actress and dancer. Her acting career began after winning the 5th season of the [[Fox Broadcasting Company|Fox]] television show ''[[So You Think You Can Dance (US)|So You Think You Can Dance]]''.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.nydailynews.com/entertainment/tv-movies/jeanine-mason-dance-winner-article-1.398764|title=Jeanine Mason is 'So You Think You Can Dance' winner|last=SMITH|first=OLIVIA|website=nydailynews.com|access-date=2019-07-05}}</ref> She is best known for her role as Liz Ortecho in the CW's drama series ''[[Roswell, New Mexico (TV series)|Roswell, New Mexico]]''. \n\nMason had a recurring role as Dr. Sam Bello on ABC's popular medical drama ''[[Grey's Anatomy]]''.  She has also appeared in various TV series such as [[ABC Family]]\u2019s ''[[Bunheads]]'', [[American Broadcasting Company|ABC]] biblical drama ''[[Of Kings and Prophets]]'' opposite [[Ray Winstone]], ''[[You\u2019re the Worst]]'', ''[[Awkward (TV series)|Awkward]]'', [[TNT (U.S. TV network)|TNT]]\u2019s ''[[Major Crimes (TV series)|Major Crimes]]'', ''[[NCIS: Los Angeles]], [[CSI: Crime Scene Investigation|CSI]]'' and [[Nickelodeon]]\u2019s ''[[Big Time Rush]]''.\n\nMason became the first [[Cuban American]] to win ''So You Think You Can Dance''. Her film credits include the thriller Default<ref>{{Citation|title=Default|url=http://www.imdb.com/title/tt1871257/|access-date=2019-01-29}}</ref> opposite [[David Oyelowo]] and The Archer<ref>{{Citation|title=The Archer|url=http://www.imdb.com/title/tt5806646/|access-date=2019-01-29}}</ref> opposite Bailey Noble. \n\nOn stage, she was last seen in Center Theatre Group's 2017 revival of Zoot Suit directed by playwright Luis Valdez opposite [[Demi\u00e1n Bichir|Demian Bichir]].\n\n==Biography==\nMason was born in [[Miami, Florida]], and grew up in a dance-oriented family in [[Pinecrest, Florida|Pinecrest]]. Both of her parents are of Cuban descent.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.latina.com/blogs/vivo-por-tivo/sytycd-winner-jeanine-mason-i-was-horrific-dancer|title=\"SYTYCD\" Winner Jeanine Mason: \"I Was a Horrific Dancer!\"|website=Latina.com|accessdate=21 August 2017}}</ref> Mason began her dance training at the age of three<ref name=sytycd>[http://www.people.com/people/article/0,,20422130,00.html \"Jeanine Mason Knows She Can Dance\"] People Magazine. August 7, 2009. Retrieved 17 April 2011</ref> in ballet and flamenco, and went on to study jazz, acrobatics, hip-hop, modern, and contemporary dance. Mason began her study of theatre at age 11 with community and middle school productions. Upon moving to [[Los Angeles, California]], Mason continues to study theater while also keeping a focus on film and Television at The [[Michael Woolson]] Studio.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://michaelwoolson.com/clients |title=Our Clients &#124; The Michael Woolson Studio |publisher=Michaelwoolson.com |date=2013-01-18 |accessdate=2014-08-10}}</ref>  Jeanine graduated cum laude from [[UCLA]] in the Spring of 2014 and accredits the knowledge that she has attained at the school to fueling her creative work. \"It\u2019s always interesting to me how my studies mirror my life. Any time I\u2019m learning new academic material, I find a way to use it in my work. And the more material I have to pull from, the richer that work becomes.\"<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.dancespirit.com/2012/09/jeanine-mason-why-i-chose-college/ |title=Jeanine Mason: Why I Chose College |publisher=Dance Spirit |date=2012-09-10 |accessdate=2014-08-10}}</ref>\n\n==Career==\n===''So You Think You Can Dance''===\nAt the age of 18, Mason competed on the [[So You Think You Can Dance (Season 5)|fifth season]] of the show ''[[So You Think You Can Dance (U.S. TV series)|So You Think You Can Dance]]'', becoming the youngest winner in the history of the competition over fellow contestants Brandon Bryant, Kayla Radomski, and Evan Kasprzak. For the first five weeks of the competition (Top 20 to Top 12), Mason was partnered with Phillip Chbeeb. During the show's sixth week (Top 10), Mason danced a contemporary number choreographed by [[Travis Wall]] and was partnered with Jason Glover. Later, Mason was also partnered with Brandon Bryant, Ade Obayomi, Evan Kasprzak, and Kayla Radomski. Mason was consistently praised for her strong and versatile performances.{{Citation needed|date=August 2009}}\n\nDuring the fall of 2009, Mason toured the United States with the top twelve dancers of the ''So You Think You Can Dance'' competition.<ref name=top10>{{cite web|url=http://fox.com/blogs/dance/2009/07/08/so-you-think-you-can-dance-tour-2009/|title=So You Think You Can Dance - So You Think You Can Dance Tour 2009|date=12 July 2009|website=Web.archive.org|accessdate=21 August 2017|url-status=dead|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20090712002429/http://fox.com/blogs/dance/2009/07/08/so-you-think-you-can-dance-tour-2009/|archivedate=12 July 2009}}</ref>\n\n===Acting career===\nShortly after completing ''So You Think You Can Dance'', Mason turned her full attention to channeling her performing skills into her other lifelong love, the craft of acting. Her on-screen career began when Mason starred in the Halloween episode of Nickelodeon's hit show, ''[[Big Time Rush]]''. From there, she appeared in ''[[The Bling Ring]]'', ''[[CSI: Crime Scene Investigation]]'', ''[[The Fresh Beat Band]]'', and ''[[Hollywood Heights (TV series)|Hollywood Heights]]'' before landing the recurring role of Cozzette on [[Freeform (TV channel)|ABC Family]]\u2019s ''[[Bunheads]]'' and leading roles in ''Hot Mess'', and ''Delirium''. She has also booked roles on ''[[Major Crimes (TV series)|Major Crimes]]'' and ''[[Secret Life of the American Teenager]]'' as well as several smaller, independent projects. Mason had a recurring role on [[American Broadcasting Company|ABC]]'s hit medical drama ''[[Grey's Anatomy]]'' as Dr. Sam Bello.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://ew.com/tv/2017/10/09/greys-anatomy-season-14-new-interns/|title=Grey's Anatomy: Meet the new interns|publisher=[[Entertainment Weekly]]|date=May 25, 2011|accessdate=May 13, 2018}}</ref>\n\nIn February 2018, it was announced that she joined the pilot of ''[[Roswell, New Mexico (TV series)|Roswell, New Mexico]]'' as Liz Ortecho.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://deadline.com/2018/01/roswell-reboot-p-greg-berlanti-rob-thomas-6-cw-pilot-orders-record-total-of-9-pilots-1202274800/|title='Roswell' Reboot, Projects Produced By Greg Berlanti & Rob Thomas Among 6 CW Pilot Orders For Record Total Of 9 Pilots|last=Andreeva|first=Nellie|publisher=[[Deadline Hollywood]]|date=January 30, 2018|accessdate=May 10, 2018}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://deadline.com/2018/02/roswell-jeanine-mason-cast-the-lead-the-cw-reboot-pilot-1202292358/|title=\u2018Roswell\u2019: Jeanine Mason Cast As the Lead Of the CW Reboot Pilot|last=Andreeva|first=Nellie|work=[[Deadline Hollywood|Deadline]]|date=February 16, 2018|accessdate=May 10, 2018}}</ref> The CW ordered the show to series on May 11, 2018.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://deadline.com/2018/05/the-cw-picks-up-charmed-roswell-reboots-tvd-originals-offshoot-ilegacies-n-the-dark-greg-berlanti-pilot-to-series-1202388840/|title=The CW Picks Up \u2018Charmed\u2019 & \u2018Roswell\u2019 Reboots, \u2018TVD\u2019/\u2019Originals Offshoot, \u2018In The Dark\u2019 & Greg Berlanti Pilot To Series|last=Petski|first=Denise|website=[[Deadline Hollywood]]|date=May 11, 2018|accessdate=May 11, 2018}}</ref>\n\nMason performed on November 29, 2009 at the Dizzy Feet Gala in Los Angeles, California at the Kodak Theater. She and Jason Glover performed their popular contemporary piece, \"If It Kills Me\", choreographed by Travis Wall, and originally performed Top 10 week on SYTYCD.<ref name=dizzyfeet>{{cite web|url=http://new.music.yahoo.com/blogs/realityrocks/297068/the-dizzy-feet-gala-dance-gives-back/|title=The Dizzy Feet Gala: Dance Gives Back - Reality Rocks|date=6 December 2009|website=Web.archive.org|accessdate=21 August 2017|url-status=bot: unknown|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20091206075757/http://new.music.yahoo.com/blogs/realityrocks/297068/the-dizzy-feet-gala-dance-gives-back/|archivedate=6 December 2009}}</ref> Glover has described Mason as \"Unique. You just don\u2019t find dancers like her. She has beautiful lines, is funky and charismatic, and has so much life onstage. Not only does it show in her movement but also on her face. Jeanine is a brilliant performer and one of my favorite people to watch \u2014 not just in our group, but out of any dancer I've seen, from Gregory Hines to Gene Kelly.\"<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.dancespirit.com/2011/05/americas_sweetheart/|title=America\u2019s Sweetheart|publisher=Dance Spirit |date=2017-10-09|accessdate=2017-11-19}}</ref>\n\nOn November 9, 2010, Mason performed a contemporary-ballroom dance with [[Mark Ballas]] to [[John Legend]]'s \"Ordinary People\" on the television show, ''[[Dancing With the Stars]]''.\n\nHer sister, Alexis, also auditioned for the [[So You Think You Can Dance (season 8)|eighth season]] of ''So You Think You Can Dance'', and made it to the final solo performances before Top 20 in [[Las Vegas Valley|Vegas]].\n\n===Performances===\n{| class=\"wikitable\"\n|-\n! Week\n! Partner\n! Dance\n! Song\n! Result\n|-\n| style=\"text-align:center;\"|1\n| style=\"text-align:center;\" rowspan=\"8\"|Phillip Chbeeb\n| style=\"text-align:center;\"|[[Hip-Hop]]\n|\"[[Mad (song)|Mad]]\"\u2014[[Ne-Yo]]\u2020\n| style=\"text-align:center;\"|Safe\n|-\n| style=\"text-align:center;\"|2\n| style=\"text-align:center;\"|[[Tango (ballroom)|Tango]]\n|\"Violento (Up Mix)\"\u2014Bailongo!\n| style=\"text-align:center;\"|Safe\n|-\n| style=\"text-align:center;\"|3\n| style=\"text-align:center;\"|[[Broadway theatre|Broadway]]\n|\"Moses Supposes\"\u2014from\u201d[[Singin' in the Rain]]\u201d\n| style=\"text-align:center;\"|Safe\n|-\n| style=\"text-align:center;\" rowspan=\"2\"|4\n| style=\"text-align:center;\"|[[Hip-Hop]]\n|\"[[Love Lockdown]]\"\u2014[[Kanye West]]\n| style=\"text-align:center;\" rowspan=\"2\"|Bottom 3\n|-\n| style=\"text-align:center;\"|Results show solo\n|\"[[Moonlight Sonata]]\"\u2014Smart Sleep With Classical\n|-\n| style=\"text-align:center;\" rowspan=\"3\"|5\n| style=\"text-align:center;\"|[[Russia]]n [[folk dance]]\n|\"[[Kalinka (song)|Kalinka]]\"\u2014[[Barynya]]\n| style=\"text-align:center;\" rowspan=\"3\"|Bottom 3\n|-\n| style=\"text-align:center;\"|[[Jive (dance)|Jive]]\n|\"[[Stuff Like That There]]\"\u2014[[Bette Midler]]\n|-\n| style=\"text-align:center;\"|Results show solo\n|\"Baby's Romance\"\u2014[[Chris Garneau]]\n|-\n| style=\"text-align:center;\" rowspan=\"2\"|6\n| style=\"text-align:center;\"|Jason Glover\n| style=\"text-align:center;\"|[[Contemporary dance|Contemporary]]\n|\"If It Kills Me (The Casa Nova Sessions)\"\u2014[[Jason Mraz]]\n| style=\"te